fulltitle: My Kris Kremers & Lisanne Froon Analyst and Theory (Foul Play)

comments.text: Very well narrated. And that's also what I suspect happened. To me, the biggest clue that it was foul play is that these girls used to document and journal each one of their experiences and feelings. Had they been lost and thought they were going to die, they would have used those devices to record a voice message, type a note or video themselves talking about their situation.

comments.text:
Dutch woman who has traveled like this in the past : your way of thinking is similar to mine. Except I have never experienced losing photos due to digital camera malfunction back then. Panama made it very hard for us, before we had permission to search and acces. I believe maybe also trying to safe face for tourists. As a young woman traveling alone, I have experience being lured away by a man with bad intentions. Every country has its preditors. And they know what the best vulnerable areas are.  Luckily I was saved by locals. But with some kind of weapon a predator could easily force those girls. Btw my preditor wasn't even concerned of getting caught or if i would have a phone or camera. They have no fear or worries. Why should they ? No phone reception there and maybe wearing a mask and planning to have no eyewitnesses. They can  easily delete the one photo of himself or a clue. After all after he is done he could left them to let dehydration take its course or tied up whatever. Made sure to cover tracks when he came back. And stage the scene. 
Ive heard in one theory that sunlight can bleach and in another theory that after finding bones the Panam. investigators  searching for evidence boiled it. But I myself never heard of such an investigation.
No bruises or scratches on bones, so that makes a big accident or falling of great hights very unlikely.
When you're lost, you try to call-no reception. Your friend is immediately going to try her phone first. And only after a few tries on different areas wil you go away alone and climb on a hill. So they would have been seperated before the first call or you have to try and call when your preditors is not looking. During many days no phone usage would have been when phones were taken away and returned when (almost) dead.
A skeleton is in my opinion very well connected, it wouldn't be parted this way due to a river.
Btw backpack was found upstream so that was weird.
And foot was separated by a clean cut, so not due to animals either
comments.author: @user-fu7ln4yi4v

comments.text: They decided to only turn the phones on to call 911/112. Very smart ladies. I would do the same. You never know how  long you'll be there in the jungle.

Apparently she'd had a hockey injury sometimes before their travels...weakening that leg maybe ?  Oh, if only we knew what really happened.

comments.text:
As someone who comes from the jungles of Papua New Guinea, it's very obvious that these girls were abducted by some people.

They were kept in a safe house somewhere in the jungle and maybe tortured and raped by some unscrupulous lunatic men.

They were killed in that safe house, but because many people in the jungle communities knew what happened, the killers tried to decompose their bodies using acid.

That how the backpacke, phones, camera were kept hidden safely in someone's house, before they placed it near people's gardens or farms for easy identication.

For this heinous crime to be hidden this long, the culprits could be well-known people around that vicinity or known criminals around the area.

If an investigation was to be conducted now, many people will reveal the culprits and the case will be closed honorably.

May their innocent souls rest in peace.
